 I do not agree that health care should be a "right" provided for by the goverment of any kind. It cracks me up how people think it is more "civilized" to pay for things for those "less fortunate". Let the "less fortunate" do productive things with their time rather than things detrimental to their health. I happen to know many people of the "less fortunate" category. Many do irresponsible things such as gamble with the money they DO get, then wonder where their money goes. Sorry, I am pissed about other people wanting me to pay for others that are irresponsible, then try to make me feel guilty about it.
<br />

<br />
 After seeing what "poor" people do with their money first hand, I am completely convinced that it costs more to keep stupid people alive than smart people. This is simply due to the fact they have to pay more for entertainment, since they have no capacity to entertain themselves cheaply (like read a book, play games etc). Instead they gamble like I said, frequent bars, and do stupid things like run up enormous cell phone bills (yes, stupid and poor people have them now too). 
<br />

<br />
 Now before anyone says that I am wanting to "kill off" these types, that is not what I am saying at all. I am just saying I do not want money yanked from my check to pay for them. And don't try to give me that garbage about how we need to help the "deserving" in spite of this. I would venture there are many more people in the "stupid" category than there are in the "responsible and deserving" category who "need" this health care the socialists so desperately want "for us".<br />
