				<div class="postbody">
				I stated this in another thread, but Healthcare needs to be a bigger issue in this election.
<br />

<br />
The EQ crowd is mostly 18 to 29 and don't think healthcare won't affect them since they are healthly.
<br />

<br />
WRONG!
<br />

<br />
As Cobee pointed out healthcare costs and monthly premiums are going up 15% a year.
<br />

<br />
We're at a point where the largest segment of the population is heading for retirement and increased healthcare needs. Those baby boomers are going to be taking pills left and right pretty soon.
<br />

<br />
Guess who's paying for this?
<br />

<br />
Everyone is including you even if you are healthy.
<br />

<br />
The big problem here is that healthcare costs are being paid as you go.
<br />

<br />
It's like not saving a penny up for college and then getting into Yale and being hit with a $35K a year on the spot. Would of been better to save $5K a year from the day you we're born, etc..
<br />

<br />
The fact is there is no savings plan for healthcare and it's just too late to come up with one now that will fix the one that is just starting to blow up.
<br />

<br />
They should have raised premiums 10% a decade ago so that all these retirees would have shared some of the burden instead of dumping it on the younger generation of working folks.
<br />

<br />
Just be prepared to start paying through the nose for the next 30 years..<br />
