				Yup, I wouldn't knock herbal medicine (at least the ones with a proven record...not some @#%$ the witch doctor sold you).  Ten years ago, chiroprators were considered shams by a majority of the medical community, and I thought the same.  Rencently though, I started developing chronic pain in my neck (my huge ego makes my head very heavy, and makes my neck hurt to hold it up) and went to see a chiro.  Twenty minutes later, I felt like a million bucks.  Since then I've made it a point to visit the chiro once a month, and get a decent massage every other week.  
