			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Time to find a new job.
<br />

<br />
If there are none available it may be time to move.
<br />

<br />
Because we are in a free market you are also allowed to find a new job as you please, this is not true in governments that need athority over the market.
<br />

<br />
You are also allowed to move at will. If the local businesses are not contributing to the community equitably with jobs, you have the freedom of movement to work where you want and in what industry.  This is not true in governements that need athority over the market.  Workforce skill pools have to be controlled.  People moving about the country need to ask for visas in some socialist states.  They are assigned jobs and housing.  In hybrid socialist states this is true only to a certain class.  Most socialist states only do this for the indigent, and the lower classes.
<br />

<br />
We call it low cost housing in the US.
<br />

<br />
When government subsidised "low-cost" housing is available, the market for housing is affected. At first there is a vacuumous bottom falling out of property values.  A massive tenement pulls the deamand from the market in the cheaper housing areas.  Landlords, not able to collect the same rent allow their properties to weather longer to keep costs down in a suppressed market.  Middle class land owners who try to earn a living by managing several properties are destroyed by their leveraged positions going off balance and banks seek to recoup on their forclosures at cut prices.  Property prices adjusting can cause a single family mortage to be reasessed at a new value, making overhang on the negative equity due immediately.  This adjustment always hits the middle class the hardest
<br />

<br />
After the initial shock to land values, property prices increase again as the market corrects itself.  Now there is a new housing standard.  New housing starts slow, and the middle class is forced to find residence in housing that is below the standard they had before the subsidies because better is not available.  Housing market picks up again but not before redefining the expectations of the class and ruining middle class property owners and filling the coffers of the bankers and high roller investors snapping up under valued property from the new and growing ranks of the poor.
<br />

<br />
Transfer the market effect to healthcare.
<br />

<br />
The service we receive by doctors now is far worse than our parents had it.  There are better medicines now, but the access to doctors for the middle class and poor has narrowed.  Subsiided healthcare here in California has really striated the market and set new norms for healthcare well below the market.  HMOs came along to let the insures compete with welfare medicine and have drawn even more lower and middle class into the type of healthcare that only the indigent were suffred with.  These programs are CAUSING the healthcare crisis.  We don't need more.  We need governemnt interference in the medical market relaxed.  Welfare medicare and HMOs always wind up making the rich richer and the poor poorer by making a bigger pool for he bottom to fall off into.
<br />

<br />
Kerry's plan is more of the same failed crap as Social Security was supposed to be.  As soon as voters are not looking congress will pass all sorts of laws to tap into the fund just like they did for social security and bankrupt it samely.  In the mean time we will redefine drasticly the classes making comprehensive healthcare out of reach of everyone but the super rich.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
